text.tspan: With this wiring pattern, input i is always the 'input from self'; input ii is always
'input from gene that is in the anti-clockwise direction' and so on. As k is
reduced below n, we keep all of the wiring available, without changing the
Attractor Scaffolding wiring, n=5, k=5. Shown with
an example state for the gene expression levels of 0x2 = [00010]
Decided on this convention for sequentially ignoring inputs
For k=n-1, each gene 'ignores its own input:
'Ignorances' are: a(i), b(i), c(i), d(i), d(i), e(i)
For k=n-2, each gene ignores its own input and the input
from the gene that is 1 step away in the anti-clockwise direction.
k=n-2 'Ignorances': a(i,ii), b(i,ii), c(i,ii), d(i,ii), e(i,ii)
NB: Input i is the MSB in the input state
and here (because n=5), input v is the LSB
